leads.lead_text: Labellum broadly ovate, concave, resembling a bonnet; leaves narrowly elliptic to lanceolate, pale green above, purple below; very rare, in far East Gippsland
Labellum more or less oblong with recurved margins, lamina straight or recurved; leaves not as above or leaves absent
Labellum erect, with a central, densely pubescent callus; plant leafless; very rare, in far East Gippsland
Labellum obliquely deflexed or recurved, glabrous or minutely pubescent; plant bearing leaves; widespread species
Labellum recurved, with 2 irregular rows of domed, shiny black calli and no apical hump; leaves ovate, dark green above, purple below
Labellum obliquely deflexed, straight, with large hump or boss near apex; leaves narrowly elliptic to lanceolate, pale green above and below
